org.hecl
Class Interp

java.lang.Object
  org.hecl.Interp
public class Interp
extends java.lang.Object

Interp is the Hecl interpreter, the class responsible for knowing what variables and commands are available.

Version:
1.0
Author:
David N. Welton

commands

public java.util.Hashtable commands
The commands Hashtable provides the mapping from the strings containing command names to the code implementing the commands. We save some space by making this public and removing the accessors.

stackDecr

public java.util.Hashtable stackDecr()
stackDecr pops the stack frame, returning it so that commands like upeval can save it. If it's not saved, it's gone.

stackPush

stackDecr pushes a new variable hashtable (probably saved via upeval) onto the stack frame.
